cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel approximation method for the sliced Wasserstein distance and applies it to generative models. It also involves deep learning techniques and experiments on image and video generation. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the proposed method is applied to image and video generation tasks. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as generative models are a popular topic in AI research. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category as the paper involves deep learning techniques. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.GR (Graphics) as it involves generating images and videos.
